HEADWORD: Champignon
<hw>Cham*pi"gnon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a mushroom,
ultimately fr. L. <ets>campus</ets> field. See <er>Camp</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An edible species of mushroom (<spn>Agaricus
campestris</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fairy ring champignon</b></col>, <cd>the <spn>Marasmius
oreades</spn>, which has a strong flavor but is edible.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Champion</ent>⟦br⟧
